97
00:06:10.612 --> 00:06:13.321
We want things to be like
relatively sized rather than just

98
00:06:13.321 --> 00:06:14.771
being like absolutely sized.

99
00:06:14.771 --> 00:06:16.987
So pixels is an absolute sizing.

100
00:06:16.987 --> 00:06:23.038
It's actually not literally pixels just so
you know, but we call them that.

101
00:06:23.038 --> 00:06:26.790
Ems is measured in relation to
what your font choice is, right?

102
00:06:26.790 --> 00:06:32.230
So if I change fonts, then I want
the sizing to be relative to the font,

103
00:06:32.230 --> 00:06:37.316
so what it actually does is it
measures the width of a lowercase m.

104
00:06:37.316 --> 00:06:39.412
That, something like that, right?

105
00:06:39.412 --> 00:06:44.331
And that's what ems is,
it's literally ms long.

106
00:06:44.331 --> 00:06:45.682
Weird, right?

107
00:06:45.682 --> 00:06:51.415
[LAUGH] But it ends up being really
useful because even if you change fonts,

108
00:06:51.415 --> 00:06:56.328
